  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Greece&apos;s Reception and Identification Service (RIS) Capability and Readiness to Manage Emergencies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since the onset of large migratory flows in the broader Mediterranean area in 2015, Greece has received over 1,200,000 migrants through its land and sea borders and has evolved from a transit to a host country. The national reception system has been strengthened to meet the needs of the growing migrant population. Nonetheless, efforts have so far been directed mostly to offering humanitarian assistance, rather than investing on the preparedness of the reception system to cope with shocks and timely recover from emergencies. Through this project, IOM is providing technical support to the Greek Reception and Identification Service (RIS) to increase its capability and readiness to manage and respond to emergencies across the migrant reception and accommodation facilities in Greece. The project will, therefore, result to improving RIS&#x2019;s risk assessment, crisis management and cross-sectoral coordination on emergencies while also helping to ensure an efficient use of resources, with a view to ensuring preparedness actions for the protection of migrant populations residing in the Greek reception system.</narrative>
  </description>
